<div id="banner">
	<h1>ACS Radio Interview</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Jeff Nicholson-Owens just interviewed me <a href="http://www.weft.org/shows/Pubaff.html">Digitial Citizen, a technology radio show that airs on WEFT 90.1FM (a east-central-Illinois community radio station)</a> about Alternative Compensation Systems. I think it went really well (perhaps my best public radio appearance yet). The problem is I don&#8217;t really have the voice for radio. But I did get to explain the idea, plug my blog and website (something WBEZ wouldn&#8217;t let me do!), and also throw in a good word for the very cool <a href="http://www.prx.org/">Public Radio Exchange</a> (a peer-review community site for public radio pieces).</p>

<p class="posted">posted December 15, 2003 05:59 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_personal">Personal</a>)  <a href="001096" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

